added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Dance Crew Edition
added.description: It's time for another Justice League talent competition and Vibe is joining the judges' panel to critique the moves of the DC universe dance crews./Robin is left without a dance crew so Vibe gives him lessons on how to be a world class break-dancer and team player.

added.title: Lucky Stars
added.description: Raven explains astrology to the Titans and tells their horoscopes, but Cyborg does not believe.

added.title: Various Modes of Transportation
added.description: With the other Titans away, Cyborg is forced to take a road trip with Robin.

added.title: Cool Uncles
added.description: The Titans take a trip to Wackadoodles, but Trigon makes Raven babysit her little brothers.

added.title: Butter Wall
added.description: When Beast Boy declares the Earth is a pancake, the Titans set sail to find out.

added.title: The Father
added.description: When Frankie attends a party at The Watterson's he realizes it's a holiday Granny Jojo made up to celebrate the day he left. Richard is feeling sad about the years he lost with Frankie so the kids try anything to cheer him up.

added.title: The Cringe
added.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

added.title: The Cage
added.description: When Mr. Corneille shows up to work with a mysterious bruise, Gumball and Darwin discover that he's teacher by day and a cage fighter by night, or was until he vowed never to fight again. However, when the school is being closed for a lack of finances the boys have to try and convince him to come out retirement for one last fight.

added.title: The Faith
added.description: Everything in Elmore is suddenly just various shades of grey, and things all over town are going wrong. Gumball and Darwin follow the mayhem and learn that one person was holding the whole town together: Alan. They have to restore his faith in the world to bring color back to Elmore.

added.title: The Candidate
added.description: When their parents all go to a charity gala at the school, the kids are locked in a classroom with a VHS tape. However, when the room starts to heat up, they need a leader to get them out of the situation and have to choose between Anais, a qualified but unpopular candidate or Gumball, a charismatic candidate with absolutely no plans.

added.title: The Magical Box
added.description: After Grizz, Panda and Ice Bear receive a special box, the brothers discover its magical ability to transport them anywhere in the universe.

added.title: Bears and the Beanstalk
added.description: The Bears work as short-order cooks in a giant's diner.

added.title: Boo-Dunnit
added.description: When the box goes missing at a haunted mansion, the Bears play detective to help uncover the thief.

added.title: The Little Mer-Bear
added.description: In order to live under the sea the Bears must transform into mermaids.

added.title: Modern-ish Stone Age Family
added.description: The Bears are invited to live with a family of cavemen but things get rocky when the bears teach the family about television.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: Craig finds himself being chased by a monster in the Creek that's straight out of the movies!

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: The Rise and Fall of the Green Poncho
added.description: Craig tries to warn his friends about the Other Side of the Creek with a tale from the Creek's defender - the Green Poncho.

added.title: Robo Teacher
added.description: When a substitute teacher fills in for Chef, Duncan thinks it's going to be the best day ever. He's wrong.

added.title: Glove Glove Me Do
added.description: Owen's newly found gloves make him great at everything. But this greatness comes at a high price.

added.title: The Tooth About Zombies
added.description: When Gwen's favorite event, the Zombie March, falls on the same day as Noah's nightmare event, dental hygienist check up day, Gwen and Noah find a way to help each other out.

added.title: Lie-Ranosaurus Wrecked
added.description: Owen pretends to be Izzy's pet dinosaur after leading her to believe she dug him up in the school playground.

added.title: An Egg-stremely Bad Idea
added.description: Hoping to 'brighten her day', Izzy and Owen pimp out Gwen's egg chair. But when it ends up in a museum run by angry chickens, they must retrieve it before Gwen destroys the daycare in a temper tantrum of unspeakable darkness.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple and Onion run out of toilet paper because Apple's been building a huge modern art sculpture with it. They're going to need more if Apple is to finish and Onion is to be able to resume his normal toilet activities.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple is in danger of losing his best friend.

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: High Stress Express
added.description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

added.title: Half-Sies
added.description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Xingo's Back
added.description: Left to entertain himself as Max takes a much deserved nap, Ben stumbles upon a Xingo arcade game and goes OE-Shock Rock to power it up, but when it receives too much juice, Xingo leaps out into the real world and our hero must go toe-to-toe with his favorite cartoon character.

added.title: Bounty Ball
added.description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

added.title: #AdventuresInBunnysitting
added.description: Zee asks Kara to look after her two magical bunnies, which quickly start to multiply, wreaking havoc all across Metropolis.

added.title: #HateTriangle
added.description: When Hal's ex-girlfriend shows up at the Metropolis High homecoming game and goes love-ballistic as the villain Star Sapphire, Jessica begins to second-guess her own nonviolent tactics.

added.title: #BurritoBucket
added.description: Babs loves her job at fast food restaurant Burrito Bucket, but her boss, who's fed up with her chronic lateness and bad case of scatterbrain, would love any excuse to fire her. When a bank robbery breaks out right across the street from work, Babs is torn between her role as a superhero and dutiful Burrito Bucket employee. Will she be able to save the day and keep her job all in the nick of time?

added.title: #MeetTheCheetah
added.description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

added.title: Together Alone
added.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: Gem Glow
added.description: Steven thinks his favorite ice cream sandwiches are the trick to summoning his magic shield but learns otherwise when facing off with an acid-spewing insect monster.

added.title: Laser Light Cannon
added.description: A magical comet hurtles toward Beach City, and Steven must dig through his father's collection of old junk, and the past, to find the weapon that can save the town.

added.title: Criss Cross Crisis
added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.title: Town and Out/Child Fearing
added.description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: Road Trippin'
added.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

added.title: Bun Bun
added.description: Finn brings a special delivery for Cinnamon Bun to the Fire Kingdom but it may come with a dangerous cost.

added.title: Normal Man
added.description: Stripped of his magic powers, Normal Man enlists Finn and Jake's help to rescue his brother Glob.

added.title: Elemental
added.description: Ice King discovers something buried deep beneath the Ice Kingdom that could change Ooo forever.

added.title: Five Short Tables
added.description: Fionna and Cake go on a cooking adventure to push Cake's art to an all-new level.

added.title: The Music Hole
added.description: While judging the hugest Battle of the Bands in the history of Ooo, Finn hears a mysterious new song.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Jeff's New Toy
added.description: Jeff wants to keep his new, flying "Wrath Hover Ginsbot" toy in its box. Clarence is desperate to play with the toy. And poor Sumo is caught in the middle.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Honk
added.description: Seeking to improve his communication skills, Clarence turns to a squeeze horn. It's really annoying.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: My Mom
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

added.title: High Score
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try to get good at an arcade game at the coffee shop to earn some respect.

added.title: Rage Against the TV
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to find a new TV in order to defeat the hardest video game ever.

added.title: Party Pete
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby look for help when their awesome house party turns lame.

added.title: Brain Eraser
added.description: Benson gets demoted and has to work with Mordecai and Rigby.

added.title: Shun and Lightning/Premonition of a Storm
added.description: Shun and Lightning: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings./Premonition of a Storm: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble. They're trapped!  Tied up with no Bakugan to help them escape, and no one knows their whereabouts. It will take some big help to help them get out of this mess.

added.title: Superstar Dan/Awesome Brawlers on Vacation
added.description: Superstar Dan: The Awesome Brawler's head to Tokyo for the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition. While Wynton, Shun, Lia and Lightning see the sites, and enjoy the tastes of Japan, Dan, as the Los Volmos Champion, has official Bakugan Battle League duties and obligations that keep him busy./Awesome Brawlers on Vacation: Lia, Lightning, Shun and Wynton explore the sights of Toyko when a rogue Bakugan shows up and rampages. The Awesome Brawlers have to spring into action, rolling out their Bakugan to stop the rogue enemy before any real damage can be done.

added.title: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition/Battle Royal
added.description: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes./Battle Royal: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

added.title: The Second Stage Begins/Mechanoids Attack!
added.description: The Second Stage Begins: With half of the brawlers eliminated, the second stage of the Bakugan Battle league begins. This round will be a timed race to the finish, with all kinds of tricks and traps that will slow down even the best brawlers./Mechanoids Attack!: Mechanoids have crashed the second stage of the Bakugan Battle League, causing all kinds of havoc. The Awesome Brawlers will now have to race against the clock, battling competitors and mechanoids if they want to make it through this round.

added.title: The Other Fight
added.description: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League. Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: A super-grumpy volcano appears in the kingdom, so Unikitty takes the gang on an epic quest to cheer it up with one of FeeBee's flowers before it erupts and destroys the kingdom.

added.title: First Flight
added.description: The gang is taking an airplane trip together, and Hawk is at the helm since today he's taking his captain's license test. However Richard is terrified of flying, so Unikitty & Puppycorn spend the chaotic flight trying to help Rick conquer his fear of flying while Dr Fox joins Hawk in the cockpit to help him pass his test. After a destructive and dangerous flight, Rick makes it safetly back on the ground (after surviving the plane crashing). Hawk fails his test but gets to take it again next week, so the gang is excited for another free flight.

added.title: Cheerleading
added.description: Brock drags Master Frown along to join him in following his dream, to become the Flyer on a cheerleading team. They team up with Unikitty & the gang and go head to head against Really Old Edith and her rival cheer team of meanies. But when the gang finds Brock is too heavy to be the Flyer they're forced to try a bunch of ridiculous ways to get him off the ground.

added.title: Ragtag
added.description: When the kingdom runs out of inspiration, Unikitty takes it on herself to re-inspire the citizens with a riveting game of kickball where she and the gang form a ragtag team of underdogs, who are supposed to win a miraculous unexpected victory against Master Frown, Brock & The Doom Lords. But when the Doom Lords end up stinking at kickball, and the people are uninspired by the good guys' easy victory, Unikitty switches things up and joins the real ragtag team, The Doom Lords, to help lead them to a victory that finally inspires the kingdom.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

added.title: Goodbye and Good Riddance
added.description: Summer's over and Ben is back at school. Unable to tell anyone that's he all these cool aliens that they've heard about all summer, Ben suddenly realizes he's gone from a "hero" to a "zero", that is until Vilgax comes after him with a vengeance. Ben must now reveal his hero side to his parents and to his fellow classmates. In doing so he saves his town and teams up with his dad to destroy Vilgax once and for all. But there is some bad news...Gwen has switched schools and is in Ben's class!

added.title: Ben 10 vs. Negative 10 Part 1
added.description: Ben, Max Ben and Gwen investigate a couple of daring break-ins, only to discover they were both once secret Plumber installations. What our heroes find out is that those responsible for the break-ins are working for The Forever King. He's brought together a rogue's gallery of some of Ben's most notorious enemies to eventually steal the world's most powerful energy source...located deep inside the Plumber bunker at Mount Rushmore.

added.title: Ben 10 vs. Negative 10 Part 2
added.description: Ben, Max and Gwen put up an Alamo like stand inside the bunker at Mount Rushmore and against great odds take down the Forever King's band of baddies. In the end, Ben goes Upchuck and digests the powerful energy source, preventing the Forever King from using it for nefarious purposes. However this ultimate baddie is able to disappear...perhaps to return once again.

added.title: From Hedorium to Eternity
added.description: 11-year-old Ben, Gwen, and friends go on the adventure of a lifetime in their own backyard.

added.title: Stuck on You
added.description: Kybher, aided by a booger-like slime biot named Skurd, attacks Ben & co, but the tables turn when Skurd gloms onto Ben!

added.title: Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: The Final Countdown
added.description: Rook and his little Plumbers must defend the Base from a mysterious lockdown.

added.title: The Most Dangerous Game Show
added.description: Ben fights for his life on an alien reality show.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Runs for President
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve run against one another in the RV presidential race.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: The Bike Ride
added.description: Pizza Steve desperately tries to prevent the gang from finding out his shameful secret.

added.title: Juntos Solos
added.description: Steven organiza una fiesta para reunir a su familia.

added.title: Escapismo
added.description: Steven usa sus poderes psíquicos para conseguir ayuda.

added.title: Cambia de Parecer
added.description: Steven se enfrenta al mayor desafío de su vida.

added.title: Antología Del Otoño
added.description: En un intento por terminar un proyecto escolar, Craig recuerda algunos de sus momentos otoñales favoritos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: A Comer
added.description: Craig ingresa en una competencia culinaria en el bosque, pero le preocupa que el nivel sea demasiado alto para él.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Monstruo De Película
added.description: Craig descubre que lo persigue un monstruo del bosque, isalido directamente de una película!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Rey Del Campamento
added.description: La familia Williams se va de campamento, y Craig y ayuda a su papá a demostrar que él es el rey de los campamentos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Caída Y Ascenso Del Poncho Verde
added.description: Craig intenta advertir a sus amigos sobre la existencia del otro lado del bosque con un cuento sobre el Niño Arquero, el defensor del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Robo-Maestra
added.description: Cuando una maestra suplente reemplaza a Chef, Duncan cree que será el mejor día de la historia. Se equivoca.

added.title: Guantes, Guantes Maestros
added.description: Los nuevos guantes de Owen hacen que sea muy hábil en todo. Pero su grandeza tiene un precio.

added.title: Diente de Zombi
added.description: Cuando el evento favorito de Gwen, el Desfile de los Zombies, cae el mismo día que el día de pesadilla de Beth, la revisión con el dentista, las dos chicas encuentran un modo de ayudarse entre sí.

added.title: El Menti-Ranosaurio
added.description: Owen finge ser el dinosaurio mascota de Izzy después de hacerle creer que lo sacó del patio de la escuela.

added.title: Una Idea Huev-Xtremadamente Mala
added.description: Esperando "iluminar su día", Izzy y Owen decoran la silla huevo de Gwe. Pero cuando termina en un museo regentado por pollos rabiosos, deben rescatarla antes de que Gwen destruya la guardería en un berrinche de inusitada oscuridad.

added.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
added.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

added.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
added.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

added.title: A Media
added.description: Durante un viaje al Lago de los Ozarks, Ben y Gwen discuten sobre la innecesaria celebración de "medio cumpleaños" de Ben. Pero cuando Max se entera de un sospechoso desprendimiento de rocas cercano, los primos deben dejar de lado sus diferencias si quieren rescatar a los mineros atrapados y revelar quién está detrás de la catástrofe producida por el hombre antes de que sea demasiado tarde: los hermanos Bugg.

added.title: El regreso de Xingo
added.description: Cuando Ben debe divertirse solo durante la merecida siesta de Max, se topa con un juego de Xingo y decide convertirse en OE-Shock Rock para encenderlo. Pero cuando Xingo recibe demasiada carga, salta al mundo real, y nuestro héroe debe quedar frente a frente con su personaje animado favorito.

added.title: Cazarecompensas
added.description: Mientras Gwen escucha una conferencia sobre el Ferrocarril Transcontinental, Ben se escapa en secreto a la tienda de regalos. Pero una vez que los Cazarrecompensas aparecen y acorralan a nuestro héroe, Gwen debe transmitir la información que aprendió en el tren y utilizarla para ayudar a Ben a escapar.

added.title: Juego Terminado
added.description: Unagami entra al mundo real y aterroriza a la ciudad de Ninjago mientras Jay, Zane y Pixal intentan evitar el desastre reuniendo a Unagami con Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: Los Ninjas están invitados a asistir a la fiesta de cumpleaños de la princesa Vania en la ciudad de Shintaro. Llevan al Maestro Wu que está deprimido.

added.title: En la Oscuridad
added.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Las Dos Espadas
added.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

added.title: Volcan
added.description: Un volcán súper gruñón aparece en el reino. Por eso, Unikitty lleva a la banda a una misión épica para alegrarlo con una de las flores de FeeBee antes de que entre en erupción y destruya el reino. Pero FeeBee no tiene ganas de compartir sus queridas flores, y trata de sabotear la misión. ¿Será capaz Unikitty de convencerla de los beneficios de compartir para salvar el reino de la destrucción?

added.title: Primer Vuelo
added.description: Cuando la banda hace un viaje en avión, Halcondrilo está al mando ya que hoy da el examen para obtener su licencia de capitán. Como a Richard le da terror volar, Unikitty y Perricornio pasan el caótico vuelo tratando de ayudarlo a vencer su miedo, mientras la Dra. Fox acompaña a Halcondrilo en la cabina para ayudarlo a aprobar su examen.

added.title: Los Porristas
added.description: Brock convence a Master Frown de acompañarlo para hacer realidad su sueño de convertirse en el volador de un equipo de animadoras. Se asocian con Unikitty y la banda y se enfrentan cara a cara con Edith y el equipo de porristas malvados que tienen como rivales. Pero cuando la banda descubre que Brock es demasiado pesado para ser el volador, se ven obligados a intentar un montón de formas ridículas de levantarlo del suelo.

added.title: Campeones por accidente

Cuando se produce un robo a un banco que está enfrente de su trabajo, Babs no puede decidir si encarnar su papel de superheroína o el de empleada obediente de La Cubeta.
